<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-03-31T19:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-03-31T19:48:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                        <head>415. Telegram 56144 From the <gloss type="from">Department of
                                State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                                Pakistan</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d415fn1">Source:
                                National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central
                                Files 1970–73, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 16 BANGLADESH.
                                Secret; Priority; Nodis. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_LLB1">Laingen</persName>; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_DRP1">Davies</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName>, Brown, and <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName>. Repeated Priority to Dacca
                                and New Delhi</note>
                            <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d415fn2">Chargé Sober was instructed
                                to inform Pakistani President <persName corresp="#p_BZA1">Bhutto</persName> that the United States intended to recognize
                                Bangladesh on April 4.</note>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1972-04-01T00:48:00+00:00">April 1, 1972, 0048Z</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <list type="references">
                            <head>REF:</head>
                            <item>Islamabad 1675</item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                            <item>Timing of Bangladesh Recognition</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>1. You should inform President <persName corresp="#p_BZA1">Bhutto</persName> soonest that we have reviewed entire matter of
                            Bangladesh recognition, giving careful consideration to his suggestions
                            on timing. We have concluded we should recognize in near future and want
                                <persName corresp="#p_BZA1">Bhutto</persName> to know that we plan
                            to announce recognition on April 4. You should caution him that this
                            information must be held in closest confidence until our announcement
                            made.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>